<title>MEXICO: GFSantander Q2 loss 18 mln pesos.</title>
<headline>GFSantander Q2 loss 18 mln pesos.</headline>
<dateline>MEXICO CITY 1997-08-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>Grupo Financiero Santander Mexicano on Friday reported a second quarter loss of 18 million pesos, and a loss of 128 million pesos in the first half of the year.</p>
<p>It gave no comparable statistics for 1996.</p>
<p>The following table gives a breakdown of the results in millions of pesos.</p>
<p>							1997</p>
<p>					Q2		Q1		H1</p>
<p>Banco Santander Mexicano	 4	     (93)	    (89)</p>
<p>InverMexico casa de bolsa     (7)	    (18)	    (25)</p>
<p>Factoring InverMexico	    2		2		  4</p>
<p>InverMexico Household	   11	     12		 23</p>
<p>Aseguradora InverLincoln	 2		3		  5</p>
<p>Afianzadora InverMexico	  2		1		  3</p>
<p>Almacenadora InverMexico	 1		0		  1</p>
<p>The bank unit, Banco Santander Mexicano, had a reserve coverage against past-due loans of 108.4 percent in the second quarter, compared with 108.1 percent in the first quarter, the banking group said in a statement.</p>
<p>The list does not include the results of the holding company, which posted a loss for the second quarter. The group did not specify how large the loss was.</p>
<p>((-- Cecilia Cardenas, Mexico City newsroom +525 728 9552))</p>
